xt\":\"**Evaluating dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about dynamic class loading and its need to reload static initialization in the correct order. Is this acceptable? I wonder if we can catch errors during testing by isolating the loading and asserting within the JVM. If we encounter an unsupported error, how should we handle it? These are all considerations that could impact the testing process and overall implementation. I'll have to keep them in mind as I move forward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Ensuring Class Retrieval**\\n\\nI need to confirm that the class initialized by `Class.forName` correctly returns a class by its name. The static initialization of `FactoryHelper` retrieves the `java.lang.ClassLoader`, as well as `SecurityActions` among others. I wonder if `SecurityActions` might need to utilize privileged methods to access functionality correctly. It’s a bit complex, and I need to make sure I fully grasp how all these components interact.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5KN36DEJ1z40AxPJ1wyWuIzO|fc_03e522aa32a0016e0169fa0532bf08819e9665bf4960816e74", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "../../source_context/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/main/extracted/javassist/util/proxy/SecurityActions.java", "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2126, "output": 1352, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27030, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777992987655, "responseId": "resp_03e522aa32a0016e0169fa051c1ea0819eb7e7d856d15bda5f"}}
