\n\n    @Test\n    void typeIndexFindsPrimitiveMetadata() {\n", "newText": "        } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n            rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void typeIndexFindsPrimitiveMetadata() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void typeIndexRejectsNonPrimitiveType() {\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> FactoryHelper.typeIndex(String.class))\n                .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                .hasMessage(\"bad type:java.lang.String\");\n    }\n\n    private static final class IsolatedJavassistClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void typeIndexRejectsNonPrimitiveType() {\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> FactoryHelper.typeIndex(String.class))\n                .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                .hasMessage(\"bad type:java.lang.String\");\n    }\n\n    private static void rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) throws Exception {\n        if (!hasUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable)) {\n            if (throwable instanceof Exception exception) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n            if (throwable instanceof Error error) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n            throw new AssertionError(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static boolean hasUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private static final class IsolatedJavassistClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing class access in instrumentation**\n\nI’m looking at a dynamic-access report regarding `FactoryHelper.class$`, which seems to be compiled with JDK 1.4. The Forge instrumentation searches for reflection calls, possibly requiring execution of the `class$` method. It appears that some branches in JaCoCo are covered, but there might be an issue with the `class$` calls being missed during the clinit phase. I think adding a test to call `FactoryHelper.class$` after runtime could clarify the results.\n\n**Exploring JVM call mechanics**\n\nIn the JVM, I can create a package-private generated caller that gets loaded at runtime and directly calls the method. This might meet the exact call site for the already-loaded `FactoryHelper` without using reflection—just dynamic class loading. But what about the dynamic class itself? Should I look into using `MethodHandles`? I need to instantiate the generated class without reflection. I’ll utilize `Javassist`'s `CtClass.toClass()` to get the `Class`, then use `Class.newInstance()` for instantiation.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03e522aa32a0016e0169fa060d55a4819ea640cbc6fa082c15\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-gYnnpgj-mIr8Ep0U7l_9w01qR-VHAnSHStekXelPzRqEJu0M19oLPueyh_49X6Ts2TRU3XJYszNZUo--saY7VMyTQ4BNFBMMPv-tkt9JOwhLG0YRptWQgg96CocQNrMuSmhZygot3F5VgRllzzS0dupdnPXnimWntGCj6sqhuXhfo01EqGHPPbk08cX_ZbqErktitwhdGJVk1A0K3KTY1_uIPDnRDsPFcWuPe-xX3T0ZW81bqzds3nQyucjSSWNFOpZK0mXOFVdyPCfihcjJ6Q0GEF_e9h1KtMeHE6aOF2RzoW5YvRvNTRy8X2-HrFjTUUYIiwD0tnEKXE4DoBWGo3bRigM9ffUsB7l2QjZG_ASN1ZTUOLHfF3ov8C_Uitimrcug94f4wpHA6O73dW2phevMvWhg9Rj0A1vPYaaIWrwJONAk3v8XLiNYVSkAGFXJAukR3eOhB_jbSEhh4gcWElzfevkW8cqDdh3LkmQCk4FXJdlr-MPCGWeilQlNfDTtEsXjTg1jcnsxRt72Nr6cI-kNtjkixqpC-AGcO6ClxTn3TWJqRC3j4CcvsErVLSdkqSyLbbprhQPEwa5Cl9xdDhsAVmX28MWRWHqyG4_TAtv9mvjDtIKNFyEVg5pw2nldv_hehNpoIfY7_ST4c4_6fjggzJIUQPVo-qae4Hgc986qRc