d directly calls the method. This might meet the exact call site for the already-loaded `FactoryHelper` without using reflection—just dynamic class loading. But what about the dynamic class itself? Should I look into using `MethodHandles`? I need to instantiate the generated class without reflection. I’ll utilize `Javassist`'s `CtClass.toClass()` to get the `Class`, then use `Class.newInstance()` for instantiation.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JJNzMSwQg1MOqqhh42beQsNS|fc_03e522aa32a0016e0169fa06278900819e8ccddd01a65ec7b8", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/FactoryHelperTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\n\nimport javassist.util.proxy.FactoryHelper;\n", "newText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\n\nimport javassist.ClassPool;\nimport javassist.CtClass;\nimport javassist.util.proxy.FactoryHelper;\n"}, {"oldText": "public class FactoryHelperTest {\n    @Test\n    void isolatedClassLoaderInitializesFactoryHelperStaticBlock() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "public class FactoryHelperTest {\n    @Test\n    void generatedPackagePeerCallsFactoryHelperClassLiteralBridge() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            String bridgeName = \"javassist.util.proxy.FactoryHelperClassLiteralBridgeForTest\";\n            ClassPool pool = new ClassPool(true);\n            CtClass bridge = pool.makeClass(bridgeName);\n            bridge.makeClassInitializer().insertBefore(\n                    \"javassist.util.proxy.FactoryHelper.class$(\\\"java.lang.String\\\");\");\n\n            FactoryHelper.toClass(\n                    bridge.getClassFile(),\n                    FactoryHelperTest.class.getClassLoader(),\n                    FactoryHelperTest.class.getProtectionDomain());\n            Class<?> bridgeClass = Class.forName(bridgeName, true, FactoryHelperTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n            assertThat(bridgeClass.getName()).isEqualTo(bridgeName);\n        } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n            rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void isolatedClassLoaderInitializesFactoryHelperStaticBlock() throws Exception {\n"}, {"oldText": "        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void typeIndexFindsPrimitiveMetadata() {\n", "newText": "        } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n            rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void typeIndexFindsPrimitiveMetadata() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void typeIndexRejectsNonPrimitiveType() {\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> FactoryHelper.typeIndex(String.class))\n                .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                .hasMessage(\"bad type:java.lang.String\");\n    }\n\n    private static final class IsolatedJavassistClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void typeIndexRejectsNonPrimitiveType() {\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> FactoryHelper.typeIndex(String.class))\n                .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                .hasMessage(\"bad type:java.lang.String\");\n    }\n\n    private static void rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) throws Exception {\n        if (!hasUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable)) {\n            if (throwable instanceof Exception exception) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n            if (throwable instanceof Error error) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n            throw new AssertionError(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static boolean hasUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private static final class IsolatedJavassistClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1026, "output": 2364, "cacheRead": 47104, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50494, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777993227418, "responseId": "resp_03e522aa32a0016e0169fa060c6044819e88ee33dcf87eccd9"}}
